		EC2(AWS)

Steps in AWS EC2
1.	Open AWS → EC2 
2.	Click Launch Instance 
3.	Give the instance a name 
4.	Select Ubuntu 
5.	Generate/Create a Key Pair (.pem) file 
6.	Keep the default settings (or select required options) 
7.	Click Launch Instance 
After launching:
8.	Go to Instances 
9.	Select the instance 
10.	Click Connect 
11.	Open the EC2 terminal/CLI
12.	Commands on EC2 Terminal
sudo apt update
sudo apt install apache2 
sudo systemctl start apache2
sudo systemctl status apache2
  Copy the Public IP of the EC2 instance 
  Paste it into a browser

